 :tx/rationale "Create task: COTX-2: Observe-crystallize cotransaction — structured observations auto-crystallize spec elements in the same transaction. BACKGROUND: Currently, observation and crystallization are two separate commands. The agent must remember: observe → check Δ-cryst → crystallize if needed. META-3 shows the feedback, but the agent still must act. The cotransaction eliminates the gap: if an observation contains sufficient structure for crystallization, the spec element is created in the SAME transaction. APPROACH: In observe.rs run(), after building observation datoms and before writing TxFile: (1) Check auto-crystallization criteria: (a) observation text contains INV-/ADR-/NEG- pattern, (b) pattern references a spec namespace (extract_spec_namespace returns non-empty), (c) confidence >= 0.8, (d) text contains falsification language ('violated if', 'fails when', 'should never', 'must not') for INV, or decision language ('decided', 'chose', 'rejected') for ADR. (2) If criteria met: generate :spec/finding entity (NOT a full INV — that needs human review): :db/ident = :spec/finding-{slug}, :spec/element-type = 'finding', :element/id = auto-generated from spec namespace + sequence, :element/title = first sentence of observation, :element/statement = observation text, :spec/source-observation = Ref(observation_entity), :spec/auto-crystallized = true. (3) Append spec datoms to SAME datoms Vec as observation. (4) Update Δ-crystallization computation: this tx now has both observation AND spec creation → delta should be strongly positive (+0.7). (5) Human output: 'observed + auto-crystallized: {spec_id}'. (6) Add --no-auto-crystallize flag for observations the agent explicitly wants to keep as raw intent. IMPORTANT: Auto-crystallization produces :spec/finding entities, not full :spec/invariant or :spec/adr entities. Findings are PROMOTABLE to full spec elements via braid spec create (which can read the finding and pre-fill fields). This prevents low-quality auto-generated invariants while still advancing the crystallization pipeline. ACCEPTANCE: (A) Observation with falsification language + spec ref + confidence >= 0.8 produces spec finding in same tx. (B) Observation without criteria produces NO spec finding (existing behavior). (C) --no-auto-crystallize flag prevents auto-crystallization. (D) Auto-crystallized finding has :spec/source-observation ref to observation entity. (E) Δ-crystallization for auto-crystallized observation is > 0.5. (F) braid spec create can read and promote a finding to full invariant. DEPENDS-ON: COTX-1 (t-222d6fdc). FILE: crates/braid/src/commands/observe.rs. TRACES TO: INV-GUIDANCE-014, INV-GUIDANCE-024, INV-HARVEST-007."
